fields.description: Adobe Express is a web application that allows you to create on-brand marketing materials, social media posts, web pages, video, animations and more with ease. See below for additional information on Adobe Express. Adobe Express is included in the Creative Cloud Suite and is available to users with an active Creative Cloud license.

Adobe CC licenses assigned to a single user‚Äôs Single Sign-On ID (SSO) and are non-transferable. This means that if you have an individual license, it‚Äôs specifically tied to the user and cannot be reassigned to someone else. Adobe CC shared device licenses, like those we use for lab computers, can be transferred from one computer to another. However, it‚Äôs important to remember that the license can only be active on one device at a time.

Adobe Captivate provides you ultimate eLearning authoring freedom. License includes access to the all-new Adobe Captivate and Adobe Captivate Classic. Adobe Captivate is only available for Columbia Faculty and Staff. Each Adobe Captivate license is restricted to installation on only one device.

Adobe Framemaker the industry-standard tool for authoring and publishing multilingual technical content across mobile, web, desktop, and print. Framemaker is ONLY AVAILABLE FOR WINDOWS. Each Adobe Framemaker license is restricted to installation on only one device.

Autodesk is a digital prototyping software—including Autodesk Inventor, Fusion 30, and the Autodesk Product Design Suite—to visualize, simulate, and analyze real-world performance using a digital model in the design process.

ChatGPT ‚Äì Generative artificial intelligence chatbot developed by OpenAI. ChatGPT can generate human-like conversational responses and enables users to refine and steer a conversation towards a desired length, format, style, level of detail, and language. ChatGPT is built on OpenAI‚Äôs proprietary series of generative pre-trained transformer (GPT) models and is fine-tuned for conversational applications using a combination of supervised learning and reinforcement learning from human feedback.

Signals ChemDraw University Edition combines the most feature-rich version of ChemDraw Desktop with integration into the Signals Research Platform. Includes ChemDraw+, a new web offering of ChemDraw allowing creation, storage and organization of chemical drawings in Signals. Includes ChemDraw Collections, ChemDraw for Excel, Chem3D Ultra, ChemFinder Ultra and Chemscript. Includes Signals Notebook Standard, the next-generation electronic lab notebook for chemists.

EndNote enables researchers, scholarly writers, students and librarians to organize their references, prepare manuscripts for publication, create bibliographies, and search hundreds of online databases and PDFs. Collaborate with colleagues by sharing all or part of your library. Automatic reference and link updating ensures data is kept accurate.

ArcGIS Online, a cloud-based geographic information system (GIS) platform, is developed and maintained by Esri. It facilitates the creation, visualization, editing, and sharing of spatial information through web maps and applications. The platform provides access to data from various sources and offers collaboration tools.
Grammarly for Education offers comprehensive AI-powered writing assistance that augments writing and learning, enabling users to become effective communicators.

GraphPad Prism is a versatile statistics and graphing software designed specifically for scientific research, enabling users to perform complex analyses and create publication-quality graphs with ease.

SPSS is a software product line for the analytical process: planning, data collection, data access and management, analysis, reporting and deployment. One license allows access to both SPSS Statistics and AMOS Statistics for departments only.
MATLAB is a programming and numeric computing platform used by millions of engineers and scientists to analyze data, develop algorithms and create models.
Microsoft 365 Copilot, your everyday AI companion that understands your work, helps you stay focused, and moves you from idea to impact with less friction and more flow.
Microsoft Project is project management software that's used to create schedules, project plans, manage resources and keep track of time..

Microsoft Teams Premium is an add-on license that enhances the standard Teams experience with advanced features for meetings and webinars, including AI-powered tools like Intelligent Meeting Recap and live translated captions, as well as enhanced security, customization, and capabilities for virtual appointments and large-scale webinars.

Microsoft Visio Plan 2 is a subscription service that provides access to both the web and desktop versions of Visio, offering advanced diagramming capabilities for complex diagrams like IT, network, and database diagrams, and including features like Power BI integration and export to Power Automate.
Visual Studio is a powerful developer tool that you can use to complete the entire development cycle in one place.

SnapGene is user-friendly molecular biology software used for planning, visualizing, and documenting DNA manipulations like cloning and PCR. It helps researchers design experiments, simulate procedures, automatically record steps, and create shareable, annotated sequence files.

Tableau is an analytics platform used to make data driven decisions. The software assists in answering questions, solving problems, and building intelligence in science, engineering, business, psychology, psychiatry, and medicine. Users can build tables, charts, graphs, maps, reports, dashboards, stories and connect to websites.
With Snagit, you can quickly grab screenshots, record your screen, and add annotations to communicate processes and concepts clearly.
Whether you‚Äôre creating tutorials, demos, or training content, Camtasia helps you deliver polished videos in less time.
